Multi-platinum selling singer and songwriter, Zahara has released the visuals for her follow-up single, Thembalam. This her third single from her record-breaking sixth studio album, Mgodi. The album shattered records in October 2017 when it went gold within the first 24-hours of its release. The singer, who is adept at matters of the heart, releases the new visuals just in time for the season of weddings and jolly celebrations. The song was recorded with renowned producer and songwriter, Mojalefa Thebe and tells a tale of trust and commitment in a long-term relationship. In the video, Zahara plays a bride whose wedding day truly is the happiest day of her life. It is set against a backdrop of unusual yet beautiful imagery for a wedding and stars Skeem Saam actor, Clement Maosa. Watch the video below.   